<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFForbes1970">Forbes, R. J. (1970). <i>A Short History of the Art of Distillation from the Beginnings up to the Death of Cellier Blumenthal</i>. BRILL. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9004006176" class="internal">ISBN 9004006176</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+Short+History+of+the+Art+of+Distillation+from+the+Beginnings+up+to+the+Death+of+Cellier+Blumenthal&amp;rft.aulast=Forbes&amp;rft.aufirst=R.+J.&amp;rft.au=Forbes%2C+R.+J.&amp;rft.date=1970&amp;rft.pub=BRILL&amp;rft.isbn=9004006176&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Distillation"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li>Needham, Joseph (1954). <i>Science and Civilisation in China (vol. 4)</i> Cambridge University Press: <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/052108573X" class="internal">ISBN 052108573X</a></li>
<li>Allchin, F. R. (Mar., 1979). <i>India: The Ancient Home of Distillation?</i>. <i>Man</i>, New Series, Vol. 14, No. 1 , pp. 55-63. Royal Anthropological Institute of Great Britain and Ireland.</li>
</ul>
